    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "The way this change is specified in the EIP is quite complicated, so I propose to implement this in a different (but equivalent) way.\r\n\r\na. `CREATE` increments the nonce before calling initcode (same as EIP).\r\nb. The distinction between `None` (not present) and `EMPTY_ACCOUNT` in the State is abolished for all purposes except state root calculation.\r\nc. When an account is set to `EMPTY_ACCOUNT`/`None` in the trie it will be represented as `None` (i.e. the key will be deleted)\r\nd. When an operation would send `0` Ether to an account it must check if account is represented in the trie as `EMPTY_ACCOUNT` and replace it by `None` if so.\r\n\r\nThe EIP explicitly specifies that the replacement in d only happens at the end of the transaction, but this doesn't matter because of b.",
